    "id": "task_20260211_a89ocf",
    "title": "bill-bot: comprehensive warning system",
    "description": "",
    "type": "code",
    "status": "todo",
    "priority": "high",
    "project": "bill-bot-1oP-Cl",
    "sprint": "sprint-1-foundation-E8UFrB",
    "created": "2026-02-11T00:36:40.067Z",
    "updated": "2026-02-11T10:06:23.389Z",
    "comments": [
      {
        "id": "comment_9c1c054e-6c20-4f04-a22b-8a5e31d02e96",
        "author": "pip",
        "text": "Spec Part 1/3 — Goal + Ingestion + Classification\n\nGoal: Build a comprehensive warning/alerting system for bill-bot that surfaces actionable risks early, reduces alert noise, and ensures urgent issues reach Bill immediately.\n\nEvent Ingestion:\n- Capture: runtime errors, command failures, webhook failures, external API failures, auth/token expiry risk, queue backlogs, process restarts/crashes, high-latency responses.\n- Normalize all warnings into a shared schema (event_id, source, category, severity, fingerprint, first_seen, last_seen, count, payload_excerpt, correlation_id).\n\nAlert Classification:\n- Severity levels: info, warning, high, critical.\n- Categories/tags: auth, infra, webhook, messaging, billing, security, performance.\n- Include confidence score + recommended operator action for each alert.",
        "timestamp": "2026-02-11T00:36:58.974Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "comment_491bd987-7ed1-46cb-af7c-db8128aef992",
        "author": "pip",
        "text": "Spec Part 2/3 — Noise Control + Routing + State\n\nNoise Control / Dedup:\n- Fingerprint by source + type + payload signature.\n- Cooldowns + burst suppression (collapse 20 identical failures into 1 alert with count).\n- Escalate only on threshold crossing (N events in T minutes), not every event.\n\nRouting + Escalation:\n- High/Critical -&gt; send BOTH Discord DM + iMessage.\n- OTP/security-style urgent notices -&gt; always both channels.\n- Add channel fallback if one provider fails.\n- Add ack/snooze support and auto-repage if unresolved after timeout.\n\nState + Observability:\n- Persist alert lifecycle states: new, sent, acked, resolved.\n- Correlation IDs and timestamps for full traceability.\n- Build views: active alerts, top noisy sources, MTTA/MTTR, unresolved critical count.",
        "timestamp": "2026-02-11T00:37:06.392Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "comment_65be873b-5e7b-4865-82fd-52e2d892e7d0",
        "author": "pip",
        "text": "Spec Part 3/3 — Controls, Testing, Deliverables, Acceptance\n\nOperator Controls:\n- Configurable thresholds and per-source severity overrides.\n- Quiet-hours policy with critical bypass.\n- Synthetic alert/test mode.\n\nReliability + Testing:\n- Unit tests for classification, dedup, escalation, fallback logic.\n- Integration tests for Discord + iMessage delivery paths.\n- Failure-mode tests: provider outage, webhook timeout, malformed payloads.\n\nDeliverables:\n- Design doc + alert schema\n- Implementation + config/migrations\n- Test suite + fixtures\n- Ops runbook (tuning, debugging, recovery)\n\nAcceptance Criteria:\n- &gt;=80% duplicate alert noise reduction during burst failures\n- Critical alerts delivered to both channels within 30s\n- Alert pipeline still works if one channel is down\n- Reporting shows unresolved critical alerts + trend stats",
        "timestamp": "2026-02-11T00:37:17.594Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "comment_c4105bd4-79ea-4f21-b335-c11e9dd4a18d",
        "author": "Bill",
        "text": "Test",
        "timestamp": "2026-02-11T06:05:54.391Z"
      }
    ],
    "position": 0
  },
